This paper proposes a new approach to pooling in convolutional neural networks (CNNs) using recurrent neural networks (RNNs). As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories within computer science, including computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, given that the focus of the paper is on improving the performance of CNNs, it is most likely to belong to the computer vision and machine learning sub-categories.
